Using a doll, the ECUP points out to the nice officer the places where it was touched, as well as several more where it would like to be touched next time, with 'Cap'n Quick and a Foozle'!

Spinning out of 'Eclipse Monthly, Cap'n Quick and a Foozle began publication in 1984 and sort of ran for three issues. Sort of, because issue three was simply called 'The Foozle' and was a color reprint of an earlier story. CnQaaF was written and illustrated by former Batman artist, Marshall Rogers.

All three issues are nestled within this torrent. As always, accolades to the creators and scanners. Reap it, sow it!



